msgctxt "dn3:1.28.1"
msgid "Brahmunā pesā, ambaṭṭha, sanaṅkumārena gāthā bhāsitā: "
msgstr "Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra also spoke this verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc35
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.2"
msgid "‘Khattiyo seṭṭho janetasmiṃ, "
msgstr "‘The aristocrat is best of those people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.3"
msgid "ye gottapaṭisārino; "
msgstr "who take clan as the standard. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.4"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno, "
msgstr "But one accomplished in knowledge and conduct "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.5"
msgid "so seṭṭho devamānuse’ti. "
msgstr "is best of gods and humans.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.6"
msgid "Sā kho panesā, ambaṭṭha, brahmunā sanaṅkumārena gāthā sugītā no duggītā, subhāsitā no dubbhāsitā, atthasaṃhitā no anatthasaṃhitā, anumatā mayā. "
msgstr "That verse was well sung by Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra, not poorly sung; well spoken, not poorly spoken, beneficial, not harmful, and it was approved by me. "

msgctxt "dn3:1.28.7"
msgid "Ahampi hi, ambaṭṭha, evaṃ vadāmi—"
msgstr "For I also say this: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.8"
msgid "Khattiyo seṭṭho janetasmiṃ, "
msgstr "The aristocrat is best of those people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.9"
msgid "ye gottapaṭisārino; "
msgstr "who take clan as the standard. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.10"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno, "
msgstr "But one accomplished in knowledge and conduct "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.11"
msgid "so seṭṭho devamānuse”ti. "
msgstr "is best of gods and humans.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.12"
msgid "Bhāṇavāro paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn3:1.28.13"
msgid "4. Vijjācaraṇakathā "
msgstr "4. Knowledge and Conduct "

# NOTE: Acc. to comm, Ambattha assumed this was referring to his own vedic lore. Hence, in the next line, I take the āya ending as locative, in agreement with yattha below.
#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.1, pts-vp-pli1.100, sc38
msgctxt "dn3:2.1.1"
msgid "“Katamaṃ pana taṃ, bho gotama, caraṇaṃ, katamā ca pana sā vijjā”ti? "
msgstr "“But what, Master Gotama, is that conduct, and what is that knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.1.2"
msgid "“Na kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya jātivādo vā vuccati, gottavādo vā vuccati, mānavādo vā vuccati: "
msgstr "“Ambaṭṭha, in the supreme knowledge and conduct there is no discussion of ancestry or clan or pride—"

msgctxt "dn3:2.1.3"
msgid "‘arahasi vā maṃ tvaṃ, na vā maṃ tvaṃ arahasī’ti. "
msgstr "‘You deserve me’ or ‘You don’t deserve me.’ "

msgctxt "dn3:2.1.4"
msgid "Yattha kho, ambaṭṭha, āvāho vā hoti, vivāho vā hoti, āvāhavivāho vā hoti, etthetaṃ vuccati jātivādo vā itipi gottavādo vā itipi mānavādo vā itipi: "
msgstr "Wherever there is giving and taking in marriage there is such discussion. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.1.5"
msgid "‘arahasi vā maṃ tvaṃ, na vā maṃ tvaṃ arahasī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn3:2.1.6"
msgid "Ye hi keci, ambaṭṭha, jātivādavinibaddhā vā gottavādavinibaddhā vā mānavādavinibaddhā vā āvāhavivāhavinibaddhā vā, ārakā te anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya. "
msgstr "Whoever is attached to questions of ancestry or clan or pride, or to giving and taking in marriage, is far from the supreme knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.1.7"
msgid "Pahāya kho, ambaṭṭha, jātivādavinibaddhañca gottavādavinibaddhañca mānavādavinibaddhañca āvāhavivāhavinibaddhañca anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya sacchikiriyā hotī”ti. "
msgstr "The realization of supreme knowledge and conduct occurs when you’ve given up such things.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.2, sc39
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.1"
msgid "“Katamaṃ pana taṃ, bho gotama, caraṇaṃ, katamā ca sā vijjā”ti? "
msgstr "“But what, Master Gotama, is that conduct, and what is that knowledge?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.2"
msgid "“Idha, ambaṭṭha, tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā. "
msgstr "“Ambaṭṭha, it’s when a Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.3"
msgid "So imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti. "
msgstr "He has realized with his own insight this world—with its gods, Māras and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, gods and humans—and he makes it known to others. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.4"
msgid "So dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti. "
msgstr "He teaches Dhamma that’s good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased. And he reveals a spiritual practice that’s entirely full and pure. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.5"
msgid "Taṃ dhammaṃ suṇāti gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aññatarasmiṃ vā kule paccājāto. "
msgstr "A householder hears that teaching, or a householder’s child, or someone reborn in some clan. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.6"
msgid "So taṃ dhammaṃ sutvā tathāgate saddhaṃ paṭilabhati. "
msgstr "They gain faith in the Realized One, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.7"
msgid "So tena saddhāpaṭilābhena samannāgato iti paṭisañcikkhati … pe … "
msgstr "and reflect … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc40
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.8"
msgid "So vivicceva kāmehi, vivicca akusalehi dhammehi, savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe … "
msgstr "Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, they enter and remain in the first absorption … "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.9"
msgid "idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This pertains to their conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.10"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ambaṭṭha, bhikkhu vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, a mendicant enters and remains in the second absorption … "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.11"
msgid "idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This pertains to their conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.12"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ambaṭṭha, bhikkhu pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti: ‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, with the fading away of rapture, they enter and remain in the third absorption … "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.13"
msgid "idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This pertains to their conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.14"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ambaṭṭha, bhikkhu sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā, pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati … pe … "
msgstr "Furthermore, giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, they enter and remain in the fourth absorption … "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.15"
msgid "idampissa hoti caraṇasmiṃ. "
msgstr "This pertains to their conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.16"
msgid "Idaṃ kho taṃ, ambaṭṭha, caraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "This is that conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc44
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.17"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte ñāṇadassanāya cittaṃ abhinīharati abhininnāmeti … pe … "
msgstr "When their mind has become immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—they extend it and project it toward knowledge and vision. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.18"
msgid "idampissa hoti vijjāya … pe … "
msgstr "This pertains to their knowledge. … "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.19"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti, "
msgstr "They understand: ‘There is no return to any state of existence.’ "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.20"
msgid "idampissa hoti vijjāya. "
msgstr "This pertains to their knowledge. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.21"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, ambaṭṭha, vijjā. "
msgstr "This is that knowledge. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.22"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, ambaṭṭha, bhikkhu ‘vijjāsampanno’ itipi, ‘caraṇasampanno’ itipi, ‘vijjācaraṇasampanno’ itipi. "
msgstr "This mendicant is said to be ‘accomplished in knowledge’, and also ‘accomplished in conduct’, and also ‘accomplished in knowledge and conduct’. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.2.23"
msgid "Imāya ca, ambaṭṭha, vijjāsampadāya caraṇasampadāya ca aññā vijjāsampadā ca caraṇasampadā ca uttaritarā vā paṇītatarā vā natthi. "
msgstr "And, Ambaṭṭha, there is no accomplishment in knowledge and conduct that is better or finer than this. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn3:2.2.24"
msgid "5. Catuapāyamukha "
msgstr "5. Four Drains "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/apayamukha-in-the-ebts-doesn-t-mean-path-to-a-lower-realm/5577
#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.3, pts-vp-pli1.101, sc46
msgctxt "dn3:2.3.1"
msgid "Imāya kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya cattāri apāyamukhāni bhavanti. "
msgstr "There are these four drains that affect this supreme knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.3"
msgid "Idha, ambaṭṭha, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā imaññeva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno khārividhamādāya araññāyatanaṃ ajjhogāhati: "
msgstr "Firstly, take some ascetic or brahmin who, not managing to obtain this supreme knowledge and conduct, plunges into a wilderness region carrying their stuff with a shoulder-pole, thinking "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.4"
msgid "‘pavattaphalabhojano bhavissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they will get by eating fallen fruit. "

# NOTE: This phrase echoes the earlier aññadatthu brāhmaṇasseva paricārakā sampajjanti
msgctxt "dn3:2.3.5"
msgid "So aññadatthu vijjācaraṇasampannasseva paricārako sampajjati. "
msgstr "In fact they succeed only in serving someone accomplished in knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.6"
msgid "Imāya kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya idaṃ paṭhamaṃ apāyamukhaṃ bhavati. "
msgstr "This is the first drain that affects this supreme knowledge and conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc47
#. VAR: kudālapiṭakaṃ → kuddālapiṭakaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn3:2.3.7"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ambaṭṭha, idhekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā imañceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno pavattaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno kudālapiṭakaṃ ādāya araññavanaṃ ajjhogāhati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, take some ascetic or brahmin who, not managing to obtain this supreme knowledge and conduct or to get by eating fallen fruit, plunges into a wilderness region carrying a spade and basket, thinking "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.8"
msgid "‘kandamūlaphalabhojano bhavissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "they will get by eating tubers and fruit. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.9"
msgid "So aññadatthu vijjācaraṇasampannasseva paricārako sampajjati. "
msgstr "In fact they succeed only in serving someone accomplished in knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.10"
msgid "Imāya kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya idaṃ dutiyaṃ apāyamukhaṃ bhavati. "
msgstr "This is the second drain that affects this supreme knowledge and conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc48
msgctxt "dn3:2.3.11"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ambaṭṭha, idhekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā imañceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno pavattaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno kandamūlaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno gāmasāmantaṃ vā nigamasāmantaṃ vā agyāgāraṃ karitvā aggiṃ paricaranto acchati. "
msgstr "Furthermore, take some ascetic or brahmin who, not managing to obtain this supreme knowledge and conduct, or to get by eating fallen fruit, or to get by eating tubers and fruit, sets up a fire chamber in the neighborhood of a village or town and dwells there serving the sacred flame. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.12"
msgid "So aññadatthu vijjācaraṇasampannasseva paricārako sampajjati. "
msgstr "In fact they succeed only in serving someone accomplished in knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.13"
msgid "Imāya kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya idaṃ tatiyaṃ apāyamukhaṃ bhavati. "
msgstr "This is the third drain that affects this supreme knowledge and conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.102, sc49
msgctxt "dn3:2.3.14"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, ambaṭṭha, idhekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā imaṃ ceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno pavattaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno kandamūlaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno aggipāricariyañca anabhisambhuṇamāno cātumahāpathe catudvāraṃ agāraṃ karitvā acchati: "
msgstr "Furthermore, take some ascetic or brahmin who, not managing to obtain this supreme knowledge and conduct, or to get by eating fallen fruit, or to get by eating tubers and fruit, or to serve the sacred flame, sets up a fire chamber in the central square and dwells there, thinking: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.15"
msgid "‘yo imāhi catūhi disāhi āgamissati samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā, tamahaṃ yathāsatti yathābalaṃ paṭipūjessāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘When an ascetic or brahmin comes from the four quarters, I will honor them as best I can.’ "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.16"
msgid "So aññadatthu vijjācaraṇasampannasseva paricārako sampajjati. "
msgstr "In fact they succeed only in serving someone accomplished in knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.17"
msgid "Imāya kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya idaṃ catutthaṃ apāyamukhaṃ bhavati. "
msgstr "This is the fourth drain that affects this supreme knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.3.18"
msgid "Imāya kho, ambaṭṭha, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya imāni cattāri apāyamukhāni bhavanti. "
msgstr "These are the four drains that affect this supreme knowledge and conduct. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.4, sc50
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.2"
msgid "api nu tvaṃ imāya anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya sandissasi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "Is this supreme knowledge and conduct seen in your own tradition?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.4"
msgid "Kocāhaṃ, bho gotama, sācariyako, kā ca anuttarā vijjācaraṇasampadā? "
msgstr "Who am I and my tradition compared with the supreme knowledge and conduct? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.5"
msgid "Ārakāhaṃ, bho gotama, anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya sācariyako”ti. "
msgstr "We are far from that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.6"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.7"
msgid "api nu tvaṃ imañceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno khārividhamādāya araññavanamajjhogāhasi sācariyako: "
msgstr "Since you’re not managing to obtain this supreme knowledge and conduct, have you with your tradition plunged into a wilderness region carrying your stuff with a shoulder-pole, thinking "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.8"
msgid "‘pavattaphalabhojano bhavissāmī’”ti? "
msgstr "you will get by eating fallen fruit?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.9"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.10"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.11"
msgid "api nu tvaṃ imañceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno pavattaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno kudālapiṭakaṃ ādāya araññavanamajjhogāhasi sācariyako: "
msgstr "Have you with your tradition … plunged into a wilderness region carrying a spade and basket, thinking "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.12"
msgid "‘kandamūlaphalabhojano bhavissāmī’”ti? "
msgstr "you will get by eating tubers and fruit?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.13"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.103, sc53
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.14"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.15"
msgid "api nu tvaṃ imañceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno pavattaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno kandamūlaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno gāmasāmantaṃ vā nigamasāmantaṃ vā agyāgāraṃ karitvā aggiṃ paricaranto acchasi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "Have you with your tradition … set up a fire chamber in the neighborhood of a village or town and dwelt there serving the sacred flame?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.16"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.17"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.18"
msgid "api nu tvaṃ imañceva anuttaraṃ vijjācaraṇasampadaṃ anabhisambhuṇamāno pavattaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno kandamūlaphalabhojanatañca anabhisambhuṇamāno aggipāricariyañca anabhisambhuṇamāno cātumahāpathe catudvāraṃ agāraṃ karitvā acchasi sācariyako: "
msgstr "Have you with your tradition … set up a fire chamber in the central square and dwelt there, thinking: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.4.19"
msgid "‘yo imāhi catūhi disāhi āgamissati samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā, taṃ mayaṃ yathāsatti yathābalaṃ paṭipūjessāmā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘When an ascetic or brahmin comes from the four quarters, I will honor them as best I can’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.4.20"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.5, sc55
msgctxt "dn3:2.5.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, ambaṭṭha, imāya ceva tvaṃ anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya parihīno sācariyako. "
msgstr "“So you with your tradition are not only inferior to the supreme knowledge and conduct, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.5.2"
msgid "Ye cime anuttarāya vijjācaraṇasampadāya cattāri apāyamukhāni bhavanti, tato ca tvaṃ parihīno sācariyako. "
msgstr "you are even inferior to the four drains that affect the supreme knowledge and conduct. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.5.3"
msgid "Bhāsitā kho pana te esā, ambaṭṭha, ācariyena brāhmaṇena pokkharasātinā vācā: "
msgstr "But you have been told this by your teacher, the brahmin Pokkharasāti: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.5.4"
msgid "‘ke ca muṇḍakā samaṇakā ibbhā kaṇhā bandhupādāpaccā, kā ca tevijjānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ sākacchā’ti attanā āpāyikopi aparipūramāno. "
msgstr "‘Who are these shavelings, fake ascetics, riffraff, black spawn from the feet of our Kinsman compared with conversation with the brahmins of the three knowledges?” Yet he himself has not even fulfilled one of the drains! "

# NOTE: This harks back to Kiṃ pana te, ambaṭṭha, sakyā aparaddhum. BTW, this is a savage takedown.
msgctxt "dn3:2.5.5"
msgid "Passa, ambaṭṭha, yāva aparaddhañca te idaṃ ācariyassa brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa. "
msgstr "See, Ambaṭṭha, how your teacher Pokkharasāti has wronged you. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn3:2.5.6"
msgid "6. Pubbakaisibhāvānuyoga "
msgstr "6. Being Like the Sages of the Past "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.6, sc56
msgctxt "dn3:2.6.1"
msgid "Brāhmaṇo kho pana, ambaṭṭha, pokkharasāti rañño pasenadissa kosalassa dattikaṃ bhuñjati. "
msgstr "But Pokkharasāti lives off an endowment provided by King Pasenadi of Kosala. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.6.2"
msgid "Tassa rājā pasenadi kosalo sammukhībhāvampi na dadāti. "
msgstr "But the king won’t even grant him an audience face to face. "

# NOTE: Is this practice attested to elsewhere?
msgctxt "dn3:2.6.3"
msgid "Yadāpi tena manteti, tirodussantena manteti. "
msgstr "When he consults, he does so behind a curtain. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.6.4"
msgid "Yassa kho pana, ambaṭṭha, dhammikaṃ payātaṃ bhikkhaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya, kathaṃ tassa rājā pasenadi kosalo sammukhībhāvampi na dadeyya. "
msgstr "Why wouldn’t the king grant a face to face audience with someone who’d receive his legitimate presentation of food? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.6.5"
msgid "Passa, ambaṭṭha, yāva aparaddhañca te idaṃ ācariyassa brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa. "
msgstr "See, Ambaṭṭha, how your teacher Pokkharasāti has wronged you. "

# NOTE: Here ugga must be a noun. See my note on AN 7.67. Rajanna is used fairly rarely in the suttas. According to the Sanskrit dicts, it is the old form of khattiya. But in the Pali it is an alternative for Khattiya. Given it’s age and association with arriors, chieftan seems apt.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.7, pts-vp-pli1.104, sc57
msgctxt "dn3:2.7.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.7.2"
msgid "idha rājā pasenadi kosalo hatthigīvāya vā nisinno assapiṭṭhe vā nisinno rathūpatthare vā ṭhito uggehi vā rājaññehi vā kiñcideva mantanaṃ manteyya. "
msgstr "Suppose King Pasenadi was holding consultations with warrior-chiefs or chieftains while sitting on an elephant’s neck or on horseback, or while standing on the mat in a chariot. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.7.3"
msgid "So tamhā padesā apakkamma ekamantaṃ tiṭṭheyya. "
msgstr "And suppose he’d get down from that place and stand aside. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.7.4"
msgid "Atha āgaccheyya suddo vā suddadāso vā, tasmiṃ padese ṭhito tadeva mantanaṃ manteyya: "
msgstr "Then along would come a worker or their bondservant, who’d stand in the same place and continue the consultation: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.7.5"
msgid "‘evampi rājā pasenadi kosalo āha, evampi rājā pasenadi kosalo āhā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is what King Pasenadi says, and this too is what the king says.’ "

# NOTE: Taking this and the next as one sentence, as per RD.
msgctxt "dn3:2.7.6"
msgid "Api nu so rājabhaṇitaṃ vā bhaṇati rājamantanaṃ vā manteti? "
msgstr "Though he spoke the king’s words and gave the king’s advice, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.7.7"
msgid "Ettāvatā so assa rājā vā rājamatto vā”ti? "
msgstr "does that qualify him to be the king or the king’s minister?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.7.8"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.8, sc58
#. VAR: yamataggi → yamataggī (s1-3) | yamadaggi (mr)
msgctxt "dn3:2.8.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho tvaṃ, ambaṭṭha, ye te ahesuṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro, yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ, tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako vāmako vāmadevo vessāmitto yamataggi aṅgīraso bhāradvājo vāseṭṭho kassapo bhagu: "
msgstr "“In the same way, Ambaṭṭha, the brahmin seers of the past were Aṭṭhaka, Vāmaka, Vāmadeva, Vessāmitta, Yamadaggi, Aṅgīrasa, Bhāradvāja, Vāseṭṭha, Kassapa, and Bhagu. They were the authors and propagators of the hymns. Their hymnal was sung and propagated and compiled in ancient times; and these days, brahmins continue to sing and chant it, chanting what was chanted and teaching what was taught. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.8.2"
msgid "‘tyāhaṃ mante adhiyāmi sācariyako’ti, tāvatā tvaṃ bhavissasi isi vā isitthāya vā paṭipannoti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati. "
msgstr "You might imagine that, since you’ve learned their hymns by heart in your own tradition, that makes you a hermit or someone on the path to becoming a hermit. But that is not possible. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.9, pts-vp-pli1.105, sc59
msgctxt "dn3:2.9.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, ambaṭṭha, "
msgstr "What do you think, Ambaṭṭha? "

msgctxt "dn3:2.9.2"
msgid "kinti te sutaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ vuddhānaṃ mahallakānaṃ ācariyapācariyānaṃ bhāsamānānaṃ—"
msgstr "According to what you have heard from elderly and senior brahmins, the teachers of teachers, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.9.3"
msgid "ye te ahesuṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ pubbakā isayo mantānaṃ kattāro mantānaṃ pavattāro, yesamidaṃ etarahi brāhmaṇā porāṇaṃ mantapadaṃ gītaṃ pavuttaṃ samihitaṃ, tadanugāyanti tadanubhāsanti bhāsitamanubhāsanti vācitamanuvācenti, seyyathidaṃ—aṭṭhako vāmako vāmadevo vessāmitto yamataggi aṅgīraso bhāradvājo vāseṭṭho kassapo bhagu, "
msgstr "did those brahmin hermits of the past—"

msgctxt "dn3:2.9.4"
msgid "evaṃ su te sunhātā suvilittā kappitakesamassū āmukkamaṇikuṇḍalābharaṇā odātavatthavasanā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappitā samaṅgībhūtā paricārenti, seyyathāpi tvaṃ etarahi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "nicely bathed and anointed, with hair and beard dressed, bedecked with jewels, earrings, and bracelets, dressed in white—amuse themselves, supplied and provided with the five kinds of sensual stimulation, like you do today in your tradition?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.9.5"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.10, sc60
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.1"
msgid "“… pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn3:2.10.2"
msgid "Evaṃ su te sālīnaṃ odanaṃ sucimaṃsūpasecanaṃ vicitakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ paribhuñjanti, seyyathāpi tvaṃ etarahi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "“Did they eat boiled fine rice, garnished with clean meat, with the dark grains picked out, served with many soups and sauces, like you do today in your tradition?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.3"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc61
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.4"
msgid "“… pe … "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: veṭhakanatapassāhi is otherwise unattested. At MN 55 veṭhaka evidently means “collar”. The Lokuttaravada Bhikshuni Vinaya has a rule about this, Pn 3: https://suttacentral.net/skt/skt-lo-bi-pn3. Thullananda gets out of the water and wraps herself only in a vethaka. Here this seems to be synonymous with paṭṭaka, i.e. a strip of cloth. It is allowable if used to tie on a basket, etc. Edgerton’s BHS dict does not notice this occurrence, but says of a ref in Mahavastu “something that wraps, covers: in a list of goldsmith’s products”, noting however a number of variants. Nata is “curve”, passa is “side, flank”. MW has “flounces and furbelows”, RD “fringes and furbelows round their loins”. These are hopelessly prissy descriptions of what sounds like the clothes of a stripper or lap-dancer.
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.5"
msgid "Evaṃ su te veṭhakanatapassāhi nārīhi paricārenti, seyyathāpi tvaṃ etarahi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "“Did they amuse themselves with girls wearing thongs that show off their curves, like you do today in your tradition?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc62
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.7"
msgid "“… pe … "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: This harks back to the opening of the sutta. vitudenti vitacchenti recurs at SN 19.1, of a bird being chased and pecked at by other birds. vitudenti by itself has the same meaning at Bu Pj 4. Evidently the Buddha was pretty disgusted with this maltreatment of the poor beasts.
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.8"
msgid "Evaṃ su te kuttavālehi vaḷavārathehi dīghāhi patodalaṭṭhīhi vāhane vitudentā vipariyāyanti, seyyathāpi tvaṃ etarahi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "“Did they drive about in chariots drawn by mares with plaited manes, whipping and lashing them onward with long goads, like you do today in your tradition?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.9"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc63
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.10"
msgid "“… pe … "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: dīghāsivudhehi → dīghāsi­bad­dhehi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.11"
msgid "Evaṃ su te ukkiṇṇaparikhāsu okkhittapalighāsu nagarūpakārikāsu dīghāsivudhehi purisehi rakkhāpenti, seyyathāpi tvaṃ etarahi sācariyako”ti? "
msgstr "“Did they get men with long swords to guard them in fortresses with moats dug and barriers in place, like you do today in your tradition?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.12"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc64
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.13"
msgid "“Iti kho, ambaṭṭha, neva tvaṃ isi na isitthāya paṭipanno sācariyako. "
msgstr "“So, Ambaṭṭha, in your own tradition you are neither hermit nor someone on the path to becoming a hermit. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.10.14"
msgid "Yassa kho pana, ambaṭṭha, mayi kaṅkhā vā vimati vā so maṃ pañhena, ahaṃ veyyākaraṇena sodhissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Whoever has any doubt or uncertainty about me, let them ask me and I will clear up their doubts with my answer.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn3:2.10.15"
msgid "7. Dvelakkhaṇādassana "
msgstr "7. Seeing the Two Marks "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.11, pts-vp-pli1.106, sc65
msgctxt "dn3:2.11.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā vihārā nikkhamma caṅkamaṃ abbhuṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha came out of his dwelling and proceeded to begin walking meditation, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.11.2"
msgid "Ambaṭṭhopi māṇavo vihārā nikkhamma caṅkamaṃ abbhuṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "and Ambaṭṭha did likewise. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.11.3"
msgid "Atha kho ambaṭṭho māṇavo bhagavantaṃ caṅkamantaṃ anucaṅkamamāno bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni samannesi. "
msgstr "Then while walking beside the Buddha, Ambaṭṭha scrutinized his body for the thirty-two marks of a great man. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.11.4"
msgid "Addasā kho ambaṭṭho māṇavo bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve. "
msgstr "He saw all of them except for two, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.11.5"
msgid "Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—"
msgstr "which he had doubts about: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.11.6"
msgid "kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya ca. "
msgstr "whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.12, sc66
msgctxt "dn3:2.12.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.2"
msgid "“passati kho me ayaṃ ambaṭṭho māṇavo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve. "
msgstr "“This brahmin student Ambaṭṭha sees all the marks except for two, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.3"
msgid "Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—"
msgstr "which he has doubts about: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.4"
msgid "kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya cā”ti. "
msgstr "whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi. Yathā addasa ambaṭṭho māṇavo bhagavato kosohitaṃ vatthaguyhaṃ. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha used his psychic power to will that Ambaṭṭha would see his retracted private parts. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā jivhaṃ ninnāmetvā ubhopi kaṇṇasotāni anumasi paṭimasi, ubhopi nāsikasotāni anumasi paṭimasi, kevalampi nalāṭamaṇḍalaṃ jivhāya chādesi. "
msgstr "And he stuck out his tongue and stroked back and forth on his ear holes and nostrils, and covered his entire forehead with his tongue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.12.7"
msgid "Atha kho ambaṭṭhassa māṇavassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Ambaṭṭha thought, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.8"
msgid "“samannāgato kho samaṇo gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi paripuṇṇehi, no aparipuṇṇehī”ti. "
msgstr "“The ascetic Gotama possesses the thirty-two marks completely, lacking none.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.12.9"
msgid "Bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.10"
msgid "“handa ca dāni mayaṃ, bho gotama, gacchāma, bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Well, now, sir, I must go. I have many duties, and much to do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.12.11"
msgid "“Yassadāni tvaṃ, ambaṭṭha, kālaṃ maññasī”ti. "
msgstr "“Please, Ambaṭṭha, go at your convenience.” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.12.12"
msgid "Atha kho ambaṭṭho māṇavo vaḷavārathamāruyha pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then Ambaṭṭha mounted his mare-drawn chariot and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.13, sc67
msgctxt "dn3:2.13.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti ukkaṭṭhāya nikkhamitvā mahatā brāhmaṇagaṇena saddhiṃ sake ārāme nisinno hoti ambaṭṭhaṃyeva māṇavaṃ paṭimānento. "
msgstr "Now at that time the brahmin Pokkharasāti had come out from Ukkaṭṭhā together with a large group of brahmins and was sitting in his own park just waiting for Ambaṭṭha. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.13.2"
msgid "Atha kho ambaṭṭho māṇavo yena sako ārāmo tena pāyāsi. "
msgstr "Then Ambaṭṭha entered the park. "

#. REF: pts-cs2.14, pts-vp-pli1.107, sc68
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.1"
msgid "Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi, yānena gantvā yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yena brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā brāhmaṇaṃ pokkharasātiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho ambaṭṭhaṃ māṇavaṃ brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti etadavoca: "
msgstr "He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and approached the brahmin Pokkharasāti on foot. He bowed and sat down to one side, and Pokkharasāti said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.2"
msgid "“kacci, tāta ambaṭṭha, addasa taṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti? "
msgstr "“I hope, dear Ambaṭṭha, you saw the Master Gotama?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.3"
msgid "“Addasāma kho mayaṃ, bho, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti. "
msgstr "“I saw him, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.4"
msgid "“Kacci, tāta ambaṭṭha, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ tathā santaṃyeva saddo abbhuggato no aññathā; "
msgstr "“Well, does he live up to his reputation or not?” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.14.5"
msgid "kacci pana so bhavaṃ gotamo tādiso no aññādiso”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.6"
msgid "“Tathā santaṃyeva, bho, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saddo abbhuggato no aññathā, tādisova so bhavaṃ gotamo no aññādiso. "
msgstr "“He does, sir. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.14.7"
msgid "Samannāgato ca so bhavaṃ gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi paripuṇṇehi no aparipuṇṇehī”ti. "
msgstr "Master Gotama possesses the thirty-two marks completely, lacking none.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.8"
msgid "“Ahu pana te, tāta ambaṭṭha, samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti? "
msgstr "“And did you have some discussion with him?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.9"
msgid "“Ahu kho me, bho, samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti. "
msgstr "“I did.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.10"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana te, tāta ambaṭṭha, ahu samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti? "
msgstr "“And what kind of discussion did you have with him?” "

#. VAR: yāvatako → yāvatiko (mr)
msgctxt "dn3:2.14.11"
msgid "Atha kho ambaṭṭho māṇavo yāvatako ahosi bhagavatā saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo, taṃ sabbaṃ brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa ārocesi. "
msgstr "Then Ambaṭṭha informed Pokkharasāti of all they had discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.15, sc69
msgctxt "dn3:2.15.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti ambaṭṭhaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Pokkharasāti said to Ambaṭṭha, "

# NOTE: The diminutive ending here is the same as the in samanaka, which Ambattha used of the Buddha. As for using bloody for re; if we don’t use curse words here, when do we get to use them!
#. VAR: tevijjaka → tevijjakā (mr)
msgctxt "dn3:2.15.2"
msgid "“aho vata re amhākaṃ, paṇḍitaka, aho vata re amhākaṃ, bahussutaka, aho vata re amhākaṃ, tevijjaka, evarūpena kira, bho, puriso atthacarakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "“Oh, our bloody fake scholar, our fake learned man, who pretends to be proficient in the three Vedas! A man who behaves like this ought, when their body breaks up, after death, to be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.15.3"
msgid "Yadeva kho tvaṃ, ambaṭṭha, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ āsajja āsajja avacāsi, atha kho so bhavaṃ gotamo amhepi evaṃ upaneyya upaneyya avaca. "
msgstr "It’s only because you repeatedly attacked Master Gotama like that that he kept bringing up charges against us!” "

#. VAR: kupito → so kupito (pts1)
msgctxt "dn3:2.15.4"
msgid "Aho vata re amhākaṃ, paṇḍitaka, aho vata re amhākaṃ, bahussutaka, aho vata re amhākaṃ, tevijjaka, evarūpena kira, bho, puriso atthacarakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyyā”ti, kupito anattamano ambaṭṭhaṃ māṇavaṃ padasāyeva pavattesi. "
msgstr "Angry and upset, he kicked Ambaṭṭha over, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.15.5"
msgid "Icchati ca tāvadeva bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "and wanted to go and see the Buddha right away. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn3:2.15.6"
msgid "8. Pokkharasātibuddhūpasaṅkamana "
msgstr "8. Pokkharasāti Visits the Buddha "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.16, pts-vp-pli1.108, sc70
msgctxt "dn3:2.16.1"
msgid "Atha kho te brāhmaṇā brāhmaṇaṃ pokkharasātiṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those brahmins said to Pokkharasāti, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.16.2"
msgid "“ativikālo kho, bho, ajja samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ. "
msgstr "“It’s much too late to visit the ascetic Gotama today. "

# NOTE: Given his mood, this was very diplomatic of them!
#. VAR: Svedāni → dāni sve (mr)
msgctxt "dn3:2.16.3"
msgid "Svedāni bhavaṃ pokkharasāti samaṇaṃ gotamaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamissatī”ti. "
msgstr "You can visit him tomorrow.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.16.4"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā yāne āropetvā ukkāsu dhāriyamānāsu ukkaṭṭhāya niyyāsi, yena icchānaṅgalavanasaṇḍo tena pāyāsi. "
msgstr "So Pokkharasāti had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. Then he mounted a carriage and, with attendants carrying torches, set out from Ukkaṭṭhā for the forest near Icchānaṅgala. "

#. REF: pts-cs2.17, sc71
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.1"
msgid "Yāvatikā yānassa bhūmi yānena gantvā, yānā paccorohitvā pattikova yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami. upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He went by carriage as far as the terrain allowed, then descended and entered the monastery on foot. He went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha, "

#. VAR: te → tedha (s1-3) | te idha (pts1)
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.2"
msgid "“āgamā nu khvidha, bho gotama, amhākaṃ antevāsī ambaṭṭho māṇavo”ti? "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, has my pupil, the student Ambaṭṭha, come here?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.3"
msgid "“Āgamā kho te, brāhmaṇa, antevāsī ambaṭṭho māṇavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes he has, brahmin.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.4"
msgid "“Ahu pana te, bho gotama, ambaṭṭhena māṇavena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti? "
msgstr "“And did you have some discussion with him?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.5"
msgid "“Ahu kho me, brāhmaṇa, ambaṭṭhena māṇavena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti. "
msgstr "“I did.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.6"
msgid "“Yathākathaṃ pana te, bho gotama, ahu ambaṭṭhena māṇavena saddhiṃ kocideva kathāsallāpo”ti? "
msgstr "“And what kind of discussion did you have with him?” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.17.7"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā yāvatako ahosi ambaṭṭhena māṇavena saddhiṃ kathāsallāpo, taṃ sabbaṃ brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa ārocesi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha informed Pokkharasāti of all they had discussed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Pokkharasāti said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.17.9"
msgid "“bālo, bho gotama, ambaṭṭho māṇavo, khamatu bhavaṃ gotamo ambaṭṭhassa māṇavassā”ti. "
msgstr "“Ambaṭṭha is a fool, Master Gotama. Please forgive him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.17.10"
msgid "“Sukhī hotu, brāhmaṇa, ambaṭṭho māṇavo”ti. "
msgstr "“May the student Ambaṭṭha be happy, brahmin.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.18, pts-vp-pli1.109, sc72
msgctxt "dn3:2.18.1"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni samannesi. "
msgstr "Then Pokkharasāti scrutinized the Buddha’s body for the thirty-two marks of a great man. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.2"
msgid "Addasā kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavato kāye dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve. "
msgstr "He saw all of them except for two, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.3"
msgid "Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—"
msgstr "which he had doubts about: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.4"
msgid "kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya ca. "
msgstr "whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc73
msgctxt "dn3:2.18.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.6"
msgid "“passati kho me ayaṃ brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇāni yebhuyyena ṭhapetvā dve. "
msgstr "“Pokkharasāti sees all the marks except for two, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.7"
msgid "Dvīsu mahāpurisalakkhaṇesu kaṅkhati vicikicchati nādhimuccati na sampasīdati—"
msgstr "which he has doubts about: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.8"
msgid "kosohite ca vatthaguyhe pahūtajivhatāya cā”ti. "
msgstr "whether the private parts are retracted, and the largeness of the tongue.” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.9"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tathārūpaṃ iddhābhisaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkhāsi yathā addasa brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavato kosohitaṃ vatthaguyhaṃ. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha used his psychic power to will that Brahmāyu would see his retracted private parts. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.18.10"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā jivhaṃ ninnāmetvā ubhopi kaṇṇasotāni anumasi paṭimasi, ubhopi nāsikasotāni anumasi paṭimasi, kevalampi nalāṭamaṇḍalaṃ jivhāya chādesi. "
msgstr "And he stuck out his tongue and stroked back and forth on his ear holes and nostrils, and covered his entire forehead with his tongue. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.19, sc74
msgctxt "dn3:2.19.1"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa etadahosi: "
msgstr "Pokkharasāti thought, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.19.2"
msgid "“samannāgato kho samaṇo gotamo dvattiṃsamahāpurisalakkhaṇehi paripuṇṇehi no aparipuṇṇehī”ti. "
msgstr "“The ascetic Gotama possesses the thirty-two marks completely, lacking none.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.19.3"
msgid "Bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.19.4"
msgid "“adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo ajjatanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti. "
msgstr "“Would Master Gotama together with the mendicant Saṅgha please accept today’s meal from me?” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.19.5"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.20, sc75
msgctxt "dn3:2.20.1"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocesi: "
msgstr "Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Pokkharasāti announced the time to him, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.20.2"
msgid "“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti. "
msgstr "“It’s time, Master Gotama, the meal is ready.” "

msgctxt "dn3:2.20.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena yena brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to the home of Pokkharasāti together with the mendicant Saṅgha, where he sat on the seat spread out. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.20.4"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavantaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi, māṇavakāpi bhikkhusaṅghaṃ. "
msgstr "Then Pokkharasāti served and satisfied the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods, while his students served the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.20.5"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Pokkharasāti took a low seat and sat to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.21, pts-vp-pli1.110, sc76
msgctxt "dn3:2.21.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnassa kho brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa bhagavā anupubbiṃ kathaṃ kathesi, "
msgstr "Then the Buddha taught him step by step, with "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.2"
msgid "seyyathidaṃ—dānakathaṃ sīlakathaṃ saggakathaṃ; "
msgstr "a talk on giving, ethical conduct, and heaven. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.3"
msgid "kāmānaṃ ādīnavaṃ okāraṃ saṅkilesaṃ, nekkhamme ānisaṃsaṃ pakāsesi. "
msgstr "He explained the drawbacks of sensual pleasures, so sordid and corrupt, and the benefit of renunciation. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.4"
msgid "Yadā bhagavā aññāsi brāhmaṇaṃ pokkharasātiṃ kallacittaṃ muducittaṃ vinīvaraṇacittaṃ udaggacittaṃ pasannacittaṃ, atha yā buddhānaṃ sāmukkaṃsikā dhammadesanā, taṃ pakāsesi—"
msgstr "And when the Buddha knew that Pokkharasāti’s mind was ready, pliable, rid of hindrances, joyful, and confident he explained the special teaching of the Buddhas: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.5"
msgid "dukkhaṃ samudayaṃ nirodhaṃ maggaṃ. "
msgstr "suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma suddhaṃ vatthaṃ apagatakāḷakaṃ sammadeva rajanaṃ paṭiggaṇheyya; "
msgstr "Just as a clean cloth rid of stains would properly absorb dye, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.7"
msgid "evameva brāhmaṇassa pokkharasātissa tasmiññeva āsane virajaṃ vītamalaṃ dhammacakkhuṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "in that very seat the stainless, immaculate vision of the Dhamma arose in the brahmin Pokkharasāti: "

msgctxt "dn3:2.21.8"
msgid "“yaṃ kiñci samudayadhammaṃ sabbaṃ taṃ nirodhadhamman”ti. "
msgstr "“Everything that has a beginning has an end.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn3:2.21.9"
msgid "9. Pokkharasātiupāsakattapaṭivedanā "
msgstr "9. Pokkharasāti Declares Himself a Lay Follower "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2.22, sc77
msgctxt "dn3:2.22.1"
msgid "Atha kho brāhmaṇo pokkharasāti diṭṭhadhammo pattadhammo viditadhammo pariyogāḷhadhammo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṃkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Pokkharasāti saw, attained, understood, and fathomed the Dhamma. He went beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and became self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instructions. He said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "dn3:2.22.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! "

msgctxt "dn3:2.22.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, just so has Master Gotama made the Teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.22.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bho gotama, saputto sabhariyo sapariso sāmacco bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca. "
msgstr "Together with my children, wives, retinue, and ministers, I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.22.5"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.22.6"
msgid "Yathā ca bhavaṃ gotamo ukkaṭṭhāya aññāni upāsakakulāni upasaṅkamati, evameva bhavaṃ gotamo pokkharasātikulaṃ upasaṅkamatu. "
msgstr "Just as Master Gotama visits other devoted families in Ukkaṭṭhā, may he visit mine. "

msgctxt "dn3:2.22.7"
msgid "Tattha ye te māṇavakā vā māṇavikā vā bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ abhivādessanti vā paccuṭṭhissanti vā āsanaṃ vā udakaṃ vā dassanti cittaṃ vā pasādessanti, tesaṃ taṃ bhavissati dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "The brahmin boys and girls there will bow to you, rise in your presence, give you a seat and water, and gain confidence in their hearts. That will be for their lasting welfare and happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn3:2.22.8"
msgid "“Kalyāṇaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“That’s good of you to say, householder.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn3:2.22.9"
msgid "Ambaṭṭhasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

